Interface RangeMapper<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of object being mapped
    All Superinterfaces:
    PlotStrategy
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabelledSetRangeMapper<T>, SetRangeMapper<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashMapper, HistoryFactory.Mapper

    public interface RangeMapper<T>
extends PlotStrategy
    Formatting object for mapping objects to time series. Objects are assumed to map onto a finite time range of the plot these methods query the overlap of an object to a time range and extract the appropriate contribution to the graph. Note we use the convention that time periods come after the start time and contain the end time.
